
NumArray is a subclass of SimpleArray that provides
definitions for an array data type for numerical data types.  NumArray
is a This code extends the vector class developed by Brian Bartell, UC
San Diego.  The constructor semantics are the same as those for BasicArray.


void plus  (const NumArray<T>&, const NumArray<T>&);
void minus (const NumArray<T>&, const NumArray<T>&);
void times (const NumArray<T>&, const NumArray<T>&);
void divide(const NumArray<T>&, const NumArray<T>&);

  Apply the operator element-wise to the two arrays and put the result into
  ArrayData.

void plus  (const NumArray<T>&, const T& );
void minus (const NumArray<T>&, const T& );
void times (const NumArray<T>&, const T& );
void divide(const NumArray<T>&, const T& );

  Apply the operator element-wise to array and the value and put the result into
  ArrayData.

NumArray<T> operator-    ();

  Negate the sign of the elements in ArrayData.
 
NumArray<T>& operator+=  (const T& );
NumArray<T>& operator-=  (const T& );
NumArray<T>& operator*=  (const T& );
NumArray<T>& operator/=  (const T& );
 
  Apply the operator element-wise to ArrayData using the value.

NumArray<T>& operator+= (const NumArray<T>&);
NumArray<T>& operator-= (const NumArray<T>&);
NumArray<T>& operator*= (const NumArray<T>&);
NumArray<T>& operator/= (const NumArray<T>&);
 
  Apply the operator element-wise to ArrayData using the array.

NumArray<T> operator+ (const NumArray<T>& a1, const NumArray<T>& a2)
NumArray<T> operator- (const NumArray<T>& a1, const NumArray<T>& a2)
NumArray<T> operator* (const NumArray<T>& a1, const NumArray<T>& a2)
NumArray<T> operator/ (const NumArray<T>& a1, const NumArray<T>& a2)

  Construct an array and apply the operator element-wise to the two arrays,
  putting the result into the new array.

NumArray<T> operator+ (const NumArray<T>& a1, const T& val)
NumArray<T> operator- (const NumArray<T>& a1, const T& val)
NumArray<T> operator* (const NumArray<T>& a1, const T& val)
NumArray<T> operator/ (const NumArray<T>& a1, const T& val)

  Construct an array and apply the operator element-wise to array and 
  the value, putting the result into the new array.

NumArray<T> operator+ (const T& val, const NumArray<T>& a1)
NumArray<T> operator- (const T& val, const NumArray<T>& a1)
NumArray<T> operator* (const T& val, const NumArray<T>& a1)
NumArray<T> operator/ (const T& val, const NumArray<T>& a1)

  Construct an array and apply the operator element-wise to array and 
  the value, putting the result into the new array.

